5:
Whoa, the Silver Woods... So this is
where the elves live.
9: It's as beautiful as rumors say.
13:
Yes, but every rose has its thorns.
This place is also called the Shifting
Woods, for a strange spell keeps
travelers away from its heart,
spiriting them ever back to where
they started.
18:
I can feel eyes upon us... It seems we
have reached the barrier.
22:
I have never known so strong a
charm to be cast over so large an
area.
26: So... how do we get past it?
30: I always just cut my way through.
37: Elves! Fair folk of the woods!
39:
My name is Lilith Stratos. I am the
last of the royal line and head of the
Resistance, which even now spills
blood in the battle against the
fiends!
40:
I have come to form an alliance. For
are not both our peoples wanderers
beneath the stars, and defenders of
all things good on this earth?
42:
What say you? Will you not join
hands with me and open the gate to
a brighter future?
46:
Hmph. I am certain the longears
hear us, but deign it beneath them
to answer.
49:
That quip's not earning us any
brownie points...
53:
If we cannot move them to kindness,
then perhaps we can rouse them to
fury.
61:
I-it's just that I have never known
Shakari to speak so strongly.
64:
Is that so? She sounds exactly like
Shakari I know...
71: It's from deeper in the woods!
91: Stand down. This is not your battle.
96: She needs aid! I can fight!
99:
You are not ready. Your sword is yet
brittle, your skills too hastily honed.
103: It is you who taught me!
106: And that is why I know best.
110:
Terribly sorry to interrupt, but would
you mind saving me now?
114:
Ignore them, Alk. We have work to
do.
